context: Regular flights to most villages and towns within the state that are commercially viable are challenging to provide, so they are heavily subsidized by the federal government through the <a0_0><b3_0><b4_0>Essential Air Service program<b4_0/><b3_0/><a0_0/>. <a1_0><b5_0>Alaska Airlines<b5_0/><a1_0/> is the only major airline offering in-state travel with jet service (sometimes in combination cargo and passenger Boeing 737-400s) from Anchorage and Fairbanks to regional hubs like <a2_0><b6_0><b7_0>Bethel, Nome, Kotzebue, Dillingham, Kodiak<b7_0/><b6_0/><a2_0/>, and other larger communities as well as to major Southeast and Alaska Peninsula communities.
